cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is about image super-resolution using deep neural networks, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and their variations, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a new architecture for image super-resolution, which involves exchanging signals between low-resolution and high-resolution states, which could be considered a form of neural architecture search (cs.NE) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on benchmark datasets and a recent challenge, which involves visual analysis and comparison of images, and thus could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM).
